$page = $_GET['page'];

if(isset($_GET['page'])){
 $page = $_GET['page'];
} else {
$page = '1';
}
Short form of above code using ternary conjuction
-$page = isset($_GET['page']) ? $_GET['page'] : '1';
-$page = $_GET['page'] ?? '1'; --> PHP >7.0 -> Null Coalescing operator


-->Used to check if value of $_GET['page'] exists by using 'isset'
-->if it is set, use that value and set it to $page. If not, set the $page to 1;
